dcm2niix (1:1.0.20171215+git34-gb641a58-1) neurodebian; urgency=medium

  * New upstream snapshot
    - addresses some defects/test failures on i386
  * debian/
    - disable openjpeg support - results for JPEG2000 might be inconsistent
      and this is a strategy which was recommended by upstream to mitigate
      failing tests etc.
  * debian/patches/up_pass_CFLAGS_superbuild, debian/rules
    - set C*_FLAGS to -mmmx -msse -msse2 -mfpmath=sse to guarantee the same
      precision on x86 platforms

 -- Yaroslav Halchenko <debian@onerussian.com>  Thu, 05 Apr 2018 09:21:42 -0400

